            <note xml:id="foot.f2">For CD’s interest in the characteristics of seedling fruit trees, see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 5, letter to <hi rend="italic">Gardeners’ Chronicle</hi>, [before 29 December 1855] (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1506.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Collected papers</hi></ref> 1: 263–4), and <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 10, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-3874.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Thomas Rivers, 23 December [1862]</ref>) and n. 5. CD discussed the peach in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref> 1: 337–45.</note>
